def: The character, personality, or office of a hostess. Shak.
Situated immediately above; as, superjacent rocks.
To go ashore from a ship or boat; to disembark; to put ashore.
Liable or subject to be visited or inspected. "All hospitalsbuilt since the Reformation are visitable by the king or lordchancellor." Ayliffe.
The doctrines or tenets of the Semi-Pelagians.
An instrument for measuring the degree of viscosity of liquids,as solutions of gum.
The process of the first growth of teeth, or the phenomenaattending their issue through the gums; dentition.
A writer of glosses or of a glossary; a commentator; ascholiast. Tyrwhitt.
